---
import Base from "@layouts/Base.astro"
const origin = Astro.site?.origin || "http://localhost:4321"
const canonical = new URL("/sample-report", origin).toString()
const description =
  "A sanitized mock example of how LyraShield AI separates scope, detected candidates, independent verification, retest evidence, and limitations."
const jsonLd = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebPage",
    name: "Sample LyraShield AI security assurance report",
    description,
    url: canonical,
    dateModified: "2026-07-16",
    isPartOf: { "@id": `${origin}/#website` },
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    itemListElement: [
      { "@type": "ListItem", position: 1, name: "Home", item: `${origin}/` },
      { "@type": "ListItem", position: 2, name: "Sample report", item: canonical },
    ],
  },
]
---
<Base title="Sample AI app security assurance report | LyraShield AI" description={description} canonical={canonical} jsonLd={jsonLd}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:py-24">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-[#365069] bg-[#07131d] p-6 text-[#edf8fb] sm:p-9">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-4 border-b border-[#203246] pb-5"><div><p class="font-mono text-xs font-semibold tracking-[.2em] text-[#54d6df] uppercase">Sanitized mock · not a real assessment</p><h1 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Sample Assurance Story</h1></div><span class="rounded-full border border-[#f3b95f]/40 px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-semibold text-[#f3b95f]">In active development</span></div>
      <dl class="mt-8 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-4"><div><dt class="text-xs text-[#91a7b8]">Target</dt><dd class="mt-2 font-mono text-sm">mock-app.example</dd></div><div><dt class="text-xs text-[#91a7b8]">Scope</dt><dd class="mt-2 text-sm">Repository + public URL</dd></div><div><dt class="text-xs text-[#91a7b8]">Result</dt><dd class="mt-2 text-sm">Illustrative only</dd></div><div><dt class="text-xs text-[#91a7b8]">Evidence</dt><dd class="mt-2 text-sm">Synthetic</dd></div></dl>
    </div>
    <section class="mt-10 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2"><div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-bg-raised p-6"><p class="font-mono text-xs text-text-muted">01 · DETECTED CANDIDATE</p><h2 class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Server credential referenced by client build</h2><p class="mt-3 leading-7 text-text-muted">The report records the scanner source, affected location, and confidence without turning confidence into proof.</p></div><div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-bg-raised p-6"><p class="font-mono text-xs text-text-muted">02 · INDEPENDENT VERIFICATION</p><h2 class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Separate evidence receipt</h2><p class="mt-3 leading-7 text-text-muted">A verified label requires independent evidence. Engine-originated confidence cannot self-verify a finding.</p></div><div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-bg-raised p-6"><p class="font-mono text-xs text-text-muted">03 · FIX PROPOSAL</p><h2 class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Approval-bound patch plan</h2><p class="mt-3 leading-7 text-text-muted">Fix PR execution stays unavailable until a server-generated patch is bound to the exact approval.</p></div><div class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-bg-raised p-6"><p class="font-mono text-xs text-text-muted">04 · RETEST + LIMITATIONS</p><h2 class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-text">Outcome with retained uncertainty</h2><p class="mt-3 leading-7 text-text-muted">A complete deterministic retest may confirm the condition absent; incomplete evidence remains inconclusive.</p></div></section>
    <p class="mt-10 rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-raised p-5 leading-7 text-text-muted">This page is a sanitized mock for product evaluation. It contains no customer data, benchmark, production result, or claim that the full workflow is currently available.</p>
  </article>
</Base>
